HEADWORD: Cercopithecidae
<hw>Cercopithecidae</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a natural family of Old
World monkeys including the guenon, baboon, colobus monkey, langur,
macaque, mandrill, mangabey, patas, and proboscis monkey.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> family <fam>Cercopithecidae</fam>.</syn>⟦br⟧
